> If someone could be so kind as to share to size of the nuts that hold my
> heaterboxes to my cylinder heads, that would be great. It could be a
> long walk to the flaps so I'd like to get them before disassembly if ya
> know what I mean.
> 
> I have an 81' 2.0L CV with the square ports. Thanks in advance...Craig.

This is what you are looking for:

http://www.germansupply.com/xcart/customer/product.php?productid=16355

Any m8 x 1.25 nut will fit on the exhaust stud threads, but these are
special nuts with a locking device, and they are small across the flats for
easier access. The torque on this fastener is only 16 ft-lbs so you need the
locking type or they will lose torque.


